  "response": "Here are some lesser-known but remarkable female Indian freedom fighters:\n\n1. Rani Lakshmibai of Jhansi\n- Led troops against British during 1857 rebellion\n- Known for her courage and military strategy\n\n2. Pritilata Waddedar\n- Bengali revolutionary who led an armed attack on a British club\n- Sacrificed her life fighting colonial rule\n\n3. Matangini Hazra\n- Participated in Quit India Movement\n- Continued marching while being shot, shouting \"Vandemataram\"\n\n4. Bhikaji Cama\n- Prominent nationalist who worked internationally to spread awareness about India's freedom struggle\n- First to hoist Indian flag abroad\n\n5. Usha Mehta\n- Organized underground radio station during Quit India Movement\n- Broadcasted anti-British messages\n\n6. Durga Bai Deshmukh\n- Key figure in Congress Socialist Party\n- Worked extensively for women's rights and independence\n\n7. Sucheta Kriplani\n- Prominent in Indian National Congress\n- Played significant role in drafting Indian constitution\n\n8. Clement Nagarajan\n- Tamil revolutionary who worked against British rule\n- Lesser known but significant contributor\n\nThese women played crucial roles in India's independence movement, often risking their lives for the cause.",
